comments:
Point 1: toolbars are not recreated in the Feb 17 am build so this no longer 
occurs.  However all other tool bars and items work fine in this scenario so I 
would like to see this action support dispose such that it can still be re-
used later.  Also, the doc for IMenuCreater does not indicate that just 
because dispose is called it will no longer be used.

Point 2:  I investigated some code in SynchronizePageDropDownAction and there 
is a bug where dispose will check for null, and if not null it will call 
dispose on it, but it never sets it to null... also the get method will create 
one if it is null

see: 


SynchronizePageDropDownAction 

		public void dispose() {
			if (fMenu != null) {
				fMenu.dispose();
				fMenu = null;
			}

			fView= null;
			TeamUI.getSynchronizeManager
().removeSynchronizeParticipantListener(this);
		}

		/* (non-Javadoc)
		 * @see org.....
		 */
		public Menu getMenu(Control parent) {
			if (fMenu != null) {
				fMenu.dispose();
			}	
                ......
